// .mcp.json.example — OPTIONAL local LSP navigation via Serena.
//
// This file is NOT loaded by Claude Code. Only a file literally named `.mcp.json`
// is read for project-scoped MCP servers. This is an EXAMPLE / opt-in template.
//
// WHY DOCUMENT-ONLY (not a live .mcp.json):
//   Project-scoped MCP servers require INTERACTIVE APPROVAL the first time they are
//   used and sit as "Pending approval" until you approve them. Web/iOS cloud sessions
//   start non-interactively, so a project MCP server would never auto-load there — it
//   would provide zero autonomous value while adding a moving part. So we ship this as
//   an opt-in example only.
//
// TO ENABLE (local terminal, or a web session where you can manually approve):
//   1. Copy this file to `.mcp.json` (drop the comments — .mcp.json must be pure JSON).
//   2. Ensure `uv`/`uvx` is installed (Serena launches via uvx).
//   3. Run `claude` once and approve the server at the first-run prompt.
//
// DEGRADES SAFELY: if uvx / rust-analyzer is absent the server just shows "failed" in
// /mcp; it never breaks the session.
//
// KEEP PII OUT of any committed .mcp.json: use `--project .` (relative), never an
// absolute home path like /home/<user> or /Users/<user>. This repo is PUBLIC.
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "serena": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "uvx",
      "args": [
        "--from", "git+https://github.com/oraios/serena",
        "serena", "start-mcp-server",
        "--context", "ide-assistant",
        "--project", "."
      ]
    }
  }
}
